      <hedline>
        <hl1>Helping Mir to Soar</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Walter Davie letter on May 23 article on Mir space station</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Why can't the Mir, or its most useful parts, be incorporated into the new space station (May 23)? If I were operating a mobile home park in a hostile desert, I would gather together available resources and join them together for the greatest use. I would not be embarrassed by creating a covered passageway between an veteran traveler and a modern Winnebago.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Why can't the Mir, or its most useful parts, be incorporated into the new space station (May 23)? If I were operating a mobile home park in a hostile desert, I would gather together available resources and join them together for the greatest use. I would not be embarrassed by creating a covered passageway between an veteran traveler and a modern Winnebago.</p>
        <p>It's time that space stuff be recycled into the stuff of (science) fiction rather than being lost to friction.</p>
        <p>WALTER DAVIE  Los Angeles</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
